HEADWORD: Typolite
<hw>Typ"o*lite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ image,
type + <ets>-lite</ets>: cf. F. <ets>typolithe</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A stone or fossil which has on it impressions or
figures of plants and animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

